NO fewer than 200 golfers are expected to feature at the 24th Tiger Amateur Open Golf Championship scheduled for between December 13 and 15 at the Tiger Golf Club (TGC), Adekunle Fajuyi Cantonment, Odogbo, Ibadan. The Tiger Open is the biggest amateur golf tournament in Nigeria in which golfers compete in various categories for prizes. The captain of the club, Alfred Amubioya told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) yesterday in Ibadan that the 2019 edition would be unique because of its composition. Amubioya said that for the first time, invited professionals would take part in the tournament. He also said that participants would vie for prizes in no fewer than 15 categories. Some of the participating clubs are- Ikeja Golf Club, Ikoyi Golf Club, Abeokuta Golf Club, Sagamu Golf Club, MicCom and Country Golf Club, Ada.Others included Tiger Golf Club, Ogbomoso Golf Club and Ekiti Golf Club, Kaduna Golf Club, Jaji Golf Club, Ibom Golf Club, Otukpo Golf Club and IBB Country Golf Club. 